          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 61</h1><p><strong>Questions 31 - 34</strong></p><p>For each question, choose <strong>TWO</strong> correct options.</p><p>Write them in any order in the answer boxes.</p><p>Which two facts about the Byzantine Empire does the lecturer mention?</p><p>31</p><p>32</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    It came into being after the fall of Rome.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    In English, it is also known as Byzantium.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    It lasted around a century longer than the Western Roman Empire.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>D</strong>    It valued learning.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>E</strong>    It frequently initiated wars with its neighbours.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Which TWO facts about Greek fire do scholars generally agree on?</p><p>33</p><p>34</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    That contact with water caused it to burn.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    That it could be extinguished by sand or vinegar.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    That it was invented by a man named Theophanes.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>D</strong>    That the recipe for making it was stolen from the Arabs.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>E</strong>    That it enabled the Byzantines to win a naval battle in 672 A.D.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>",
